description:
Challenges considered will include pesticides, plastics, pharmaceuticals, food waste, genetically modified crops, and food certification.

Six student teams will be formed in each of these areas to: 
1) define the problem; 
2) assess the legal context; 
3) analyse economic benefits and costs; 
4) evaluate scientific evidence of risks to health and environment; 
5) consider ethical concerns;
6) propose public and/or private sector solutions.
